        "title": "Why Should You Consider Magento Alternatives? ",
        "h1": null,
        "style": "light",
        "decorator": "none",
        "content": "<p>Magento&#39;s monolithic architecture is highly overrated. With alternative solutions to Magento you can add more functionality to your website, while still keeping the price down. Yes, Magento is the most popular open source ecommerce platform, but that&#39;s due to the fact that when they started, there weren&#39;t many alternatives to Magento. If you don&#39;t want to be stuck in an endless loophole of expensive developing costs, poor website performance, unlimited bug fixes and configurations, you might want to consider switching platforms. Don&#39;t listen to advertisements about how easy it is to scale. Website owners have realized that Magento is a terrible bang for the buck and for the past few years, many companies have left Magento for non-monolithic ecommerce platforms.&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\nThe main issue is that Magento&#39;s heavy architecture structure requires you to have knowledge of computer engineering and structural design in order to set it up and get running. For startups this may not be a valuable investment, considering how expensive it is to hire a Magento developer that has knowledge of Java and PHP Zend Frameworks. Additonally, while having a variety applications and extensions is great, it comes at a price in terms of your website performance and overall development costs. With other platforms you get robust features embedded into the platform, omitting the need to spend more and lose performance.&nbsp;</p>\n",
